Model Schematic

Model R Functions

de_fun <- function(t, states, parameters)
{
  with(as.list(c(states,parameters)),
       {
         #rates of change go here
         dE <- muV*V + muL*L + muH*H + muEx*Ex - sigma*E + gamma*V - lambda*E
         dV <- sigma*E - gamma*V - muV*V - c*beta*V*(L + eta*H)/(E+V+L+H+Ex)
         dL <- p*c*beta*V*(L + eta*H)/(E+V+L+H+Ex) + theta*H - omega*L - muL*L - rhoL*L
         dH <- (1-p)*c*beta*V*(L + eta*H)/(E+V+L+H+Ex) - theta*H + omega*L + lambda*E - muH*H - rhoH*H
         dEx <- rhoH*H + rhoL*L - muEx*Ex
         
         return(list(c(dE,dV,dL,dH,dEx)))
       })
}

Next, we will utilize the desolve library to run our model

#define states
E <- 994500
V <- 39300
L <- 1600
H <- 500
Ex <- 13000

states = c(E = E, V = V, L = L, H = H, Ex = Ex)

#define parameters
muBaseline <- 1/79 #1 over life expectancy (79) starting at age 10 
muInjection <- .01
muV <- muBaseline
muL <- muBaseline + muInjection
muH <- muBaseline + muInjection
muEx <- muBaseline
sigma <- 0.001
gamma <- 0.01
lambda <- 0.0001
c <- 15
beta <- .05
eta <- 5
theta <- .1
omega <- .005
p<- .95
rhoL <- .1# should be 1 over length of injection career
rhoH <- .1

parameters = c(muV = muV, muL = muL, muH = muH, muEx = muEx, sigma = sigma, c = c, beta = beta, eta = eta, theta = theta, omega = omega, gamma = gamma, lambda = lambda, p = p, rhoL = rhoL, rhoH = rhoH)

#define time
t = seq(0,500, by = 1)

result <- ode(y = states, times = t, func = de_fun, parms = parameters)

We want to pull the initiation rate out of this and include it in our results as well

And now we can plot out our result like so

ggplot(result) + 
  geom_point(aes(x = time, y = E))

ggplot(result) + 
  geom_point(aes(x = time, y = V))

ggplot(result) + 
  geom_point(aes(x = time, y = L))

ggplot(result) + 
  geom_point(aes(x = time, y = H))

ggplot(result) + 
  geom_point(aes(x = time, y = Ex))

ggplot(result) + 
  geom_point(aes(x = time, y = initiation))

ggplot(result) + 
  geom_point(aes(x = time, y = E + V + L + H + Ex))

In addition we want to conduct a sensitivity analysis for each of our parameters, so we will do so for each variable here. We will use the version calculated above as our baseline :

#sigma
new_parameters_one = c(muV = muV, muL = muL, muH = muH, muEx = muEx, sigma = sigma*.9, c = c, beta = beta, eta = eta, theta = theta, omega = omega, gamma = gamma, lambda = lambda, p = p, rhoL = rhoL, rhoH = rhoH)
new_result_one <- ode(y = states, times = t, func = de_fun, parms = new_parameters_one)
new_result_one <- as.data.frame(new_result_one) %>% mutate(initiation = c*beta*V*(L + eta*H)/(E+V+L+H+Ex) )

new_parameters_two = c(muV = muV, muL = muL, muH = muH, muEx = muEx, sigma = sigma*1.1, c = c, beta = beta, eta = eta, theta = theta, omega = omega, gamma = gamma, lambda = lambda, p = p, rhoL = rhoL, rhoH = rhoH)
new_result_two <- ode(y = states, times = t, func = de_fun, parms = new_parameters_two)
new_result_two <- as.data.frame(new_result_two) %>% mutate(initiation = c*beta*V*(L + eta*H)/(E+V+L+H+Ex) )

initiation_rates <- as.data.frame(matrix(c(result$time, new_result_one$initiation, result$initiation, new_result_two$initiation), ncol = 4))
colnames(initiation_rates) <- c("Time", "Decrease", "Baseline","Increase")

ggplot(initiation_rates) + 
  geom_point(aes(x = Time, y = Decrease, colour = "Decrease")) +
  geom_point(aes(x = Time, y = Baseline, colour = "Baseline")) +
  geom_point(aes(x = Time, y = Increase, colour = "Increase")) +
  ggtitle("Sigma (E to V) Sensitivity") +
  ylab("Initiations")

#omega
new_parameters_one = c(muV = muV, muL = muL, muH = muH, muEx = muEx, sigma = sigma, c = c, beta = beta, eta = eta, theta = theta, omega = omega*.9, gamma = gamma, lambda = lambda, p = p, rhoL = rhoL, rhoH = rhoH)
new_result_one <- ode(y = states, times = t, func = de_fun, parms = new_parameters_one)
new_result_one <- as.data.frame(new_result_one) %>% mutate(initiation = c*beta*V*(L + eta*H)/(E+V+L+H + Ex) )

new_parameters_two = c(muV = muV, muL = muL, muH = muH, muEx = muEx, sigma = sigma, c = c, beta = beta, eta = eta, theta = theta, omega = omega*1.1, gamma = gamma, lambda = lambda, p = p, rhoL = rhoL, rhoH = rhoH)
new_result_two <- ode(y = states, times = t, func = de_fun, parms = new_parameters_two)
new_result_two <- as.data.frame(new_result_two) %>% mutate(initiation = c*beta*V*(L + eta*H)/(E+V+L+H + Ex) )

initiation_rates <- as.data.frame(matrix(c(result$time, new_result_one$initiation, result$initiation, new_result_two$initiation), ncol = 4))
colnames(initiation_rates) <- c("Time", "Decrease", "Baseline","Increase")

ggplot(initiation_rates) + 
  geom_point(aes(x = Time, y = Decrease, colour = "Decrease")) +
  geom_point(aes(x = Time, y = Baseline, colour = "Baseline")) +
  geom_point(aes(x = Time, y = Increase, colour = "Increase")) +
  ggtitle("Omega (L to H) Sensitivity") +
  ylab("Initiations")
